        <h2>The Idea</h2>
        <img src="{{ 'Atelier-Calla-Idea-1.jpg' | asset_url }}">
        <br><br>
        <p>Founded by Christelle Paul, Atelier Calla specializes in production of jewelry and home goods made of horn, wood and bone. Donna revived Christelle's passion after the devastation of 2010 earthquake and with determination, she quit her job to establish this company in October 2011. Her creative team now consists of 6 employees who were once jobless.</p>
      
      </div>
      <div class="grid__item large--one-third text-center">
        <h2>The Craft</h2>
        <img src="{{ 'Atelier-Calla-Craft-1.jpg' | asset_url }}">
          <br><br>
        <p>The process of this labor-intensive craft begins with food byproduct such as horn and bone. Bone is tougher so it retains a more authentic shape while the process for wood begins with sanding. The end products are both breathtaking and naturally Haiti.</p>
      
      </div>
      <div class="grid__item large--one-third text-center">
        <h2>The Impact</h2>
        <img src="{{ 'Atelier-Calla-Impact-1.jpg' | asset_url }}">  <br><br>
        <p>What to do when the young man who delivers food to the workshop just starts working without me asking and he says, 'I just want to learn the job'...that is our reality; young guys and girls who just need to work. – Atelier Calla </p>
      
      </div>
    </div>
